1
00:00:40,920 --> 00:00:44,700
<i>After The Ruin, we started over,</i>

2
00:00:44,800 --> 00:00:49,383
<i>creating a new society,
one of true equality.</i>

3
00:00:49,880 --> 00:00:52,587
<i>Rules were the building
blocks of that equality.</i>

4
00:00:52,840 --> 00:00:54,860
<i>We learned them as Newchildren.</i>

5
00:00:54,960 --> 00:00:56,541
<i>Rules like:</i>

6
00:01:01,880 --> 00:01:03,506
<i>Injected.</i>

7
00:01:15,800 --> 00:01:17,665
<i>My name is Jonas.</i>

8
00:01:17,840 --> 00:01:19,540
<i>I don't have a last name.</i>

9
00:01:19,640 --> 00:01:21,790
<i>None of us did.</i>

10
00:01:22,000 --> 00:01:25,424
<i>That day, the day before graduation,</i>

11
00:01:25,800 --> 00:01:28,302
<i>I admit it, I was scared.</i>

12
00:01:28,800 --> 00:01:31,985
<i>Tomorrow we'd be assigned
our jobs, our purpose.</i>

13
00:01:32,840 --> 00:01:35,149
<i>It seemed everyone
knew theirs already.</i>

14
00:01:35,800 --> 00:01:37,461
<i>Not me.</i>

15
00:01:37,600 --> 00:01:39,829
<i>I was lost.</i>

16
00:01:40,520 --> 00:01:42,829
<i>I always felt like I saw things</i>

17
00:01:43,560 --> 00:01:47,549
<i>differently, saw things
other people didn't.</i>

18
00:01:58,360 --> 00:02:00,430
<i>I never said anything.</i>

19
00:02:00,760 --> 00:02:02,705
<i>I didn't want to be different.</i>

20
00:02:03,320 --> 00:02:04,867
<i>Who would?</i>

21
00:02:05,160 --> 00:02:06,620
Jonas.

22
00:02:06,720 --> 00:02:07,820
I apologize, we're late.

23
00:02:07,920 --> 00:02:10,180
I got Asher to come say
goodbye to Teacher.

24
00:02:10,280 --> 00:02:11,820
I accept your apology.

25
00:02:11,920 --> 00:02:13,460
<i>Asher and Fiona,</i>

26
00:02:13,560 --> 00:02:15,460
<i>we'd been friends our whole lives.</i>

27
00:02:15,560 --> 00:02:18,020
<i>Asher was the boy who
made everyone laugh.</i>

28
00:02:18,120 --> 00:02:19,940
<i>Fiona, well,</i>

29
00:02:20,040 --> 00:02:21,780
<i>she was the girl who
made everyone smile.</i>

30
00:02:21,880 --> 00:02:22,860
Take that back!

31
00:02:22,960 --> 00:02:24,460
Whoever is listening, please, please,

32
00:02:24,560 --> 00:02:26,980
do not make me Vice Chancellor
of Waste Management!

33
00:02:27,080 --> 00:02:28,060
Please!

34
00:02:28,160 --> 00:02:29,460
<i>We lived in a world</i>

35
00:02:29,560 --> 00:02:31,460
<i>where differences weren't allowed.</i>

36
00:02:31,560 --> 00:02:33,260
<i>There was no "popular."</i>

37
00:02:33,360 --> 00:02:34,620
<i>No fame.</i>

38
00:02:34,720 --> 00:02:36,984
<i>No losers and no winners.</i>

39
00:02:37,160 --> 00:02:38,980
<i>Our Elders had eliminated all of that</i>

40
00:02:39,080 --> 00:02:41,582
<i>so there'd be no conflict between us.</i>

41
00:02:41,960 --> 00:02:46,351
<i>Fear, pain, envy, hate,</i>

42
00:02:46,600 --> 00:02:48,980
<i>they weren't words so much as sounds.</i>

43
00:02:49,080 --> 00:02:52,060
<i>Their echoes were gone,
to the other side of history.</i>

44
00:02:54,840 --> 00:02:57,786
<i>I'm asked if I should
apologize for what I did.</i>

45
00:02:58,920 --> 00:03:01,024
<i>I'll let you decide.</i>

46
00:03:02,320 --> 00:03:04,340
I'm going to miss volunteering here.

47
00:03:04,440 --> 00:03:06,460
Oh, no. If ever there
was a person born

48
00:03:06,560 --> 00:03:09,910
- to work at the Nurturing Center...
- I could be surprised, right?

49
00:03:10,040 --> 00:03:11,220
Jonas, if you had to guess,

50
00:03:11,320 --> 00:03:13,788
of all the positions the
elders picked for me?

51
00:03:15,560 --> 00:03:16,700
Nurturing Center.

52
00:03:18,200 --> 00:03:21,146
<i>Welcome to the Nurturing Center.</i>

53
00:03:28,520 --> 00:03:30,300
I got this. I got this.

54
00:03:30,400 --> 00:03:32,982
- Think heavy. Think heavy.
- Come on, come on.

55
00:03:35,200 --> 00:03:36,340
We win!

56
00:03:36,440 --> 00:03:38,060
Aren't you my chubby champion?

57
00:03:38,160 --> 00:03:39,940
- Which one was heavier?
- Mine.

58
00:03:40,040 --> 00:03:41,060
Asher?

59
00:03:42,600 --> 00:03:44,860
Father, I think Fiona put
her finger on the scale.

60
00:03:44,960 --> 00:03:46,100
I did not.

61
00:03:51,200 --> 00:03:54,431
Aw, this little guy didn't
qualify for tomorrow's ceremony.

62
00:03:55,080 --> 00:03:57,580
He's just not strong enough to
be assigned to a family yet.

63
00:03:59,040 --> 00:04:01,060
He looks so unhappy.

64
00:04:01,160 --> 00:04:03,822
Hey...

65
00:04:04,520 --> 00:04:06,590
It's okay, Jonas, you can open it.

66
00:04:10,560 --> 00:04:12,700
Yeah, it's Jonas.

67
00:04:12,800 --> 00:04:14,665
Here, let me.

68
00:04:15,120 --> 00:04:17,020
Oh, There you go. There you go.

69
00:04:18,240 --> 00:04:20,020
- It's okay.
- Some people have it, huh?

70
00:04:20,120 --> 00:04:21,260
Well, that's just not fair.

71
00:04:21,360 --> 00:04:23,021
Be strong, Gabriel.

72
00:04:23,640 --> 00:04:25,180
You looked at his name?

73
00:04:25,280 --> 00:04:26,660
Isn't that against the rules?

74
00:04:26,760 --> 00:04:28,500
Yeah, it, it is.

75
00:04:29,360 --> 00:04:31,783
I just thought having a
name might help him grow.

76
00:04:32,120 --> 00:04:34,543
So I whisper it to him
when no one can hear.

77
00:04:35,440 --> 00:04:37,305
Sometimes I call him Gabe.

78
00:04:38,480 --> 00:04:39,780
But he's usually so restless,

79
00:04:39,880 --> 00:04:42,109
I, I'm not even sure he can hear me.

80
00:04:42,440 --> 00:04:43,420
You okay?

81
00:04:43,520 --> 00:04:45,100
Huh? Yeah.

82
00:04:45,200 --> 00:04:46,180
I'm fine.

83
00:04:46,280 --> 00:04:47,820
So the old man turns
to the Elder and says,

84
00:04:47,920 --> 00:04:49,220
"Do you know who I am?"

85
00:04:49,320 --> 00:04:51,340
And the Elder says,
"Sir, I know you're old,

86
00:04:51,440 --> 00:04:53,100
but that is no excuse
for being prideful."

87
00:04:53,200 --> 00:04:56,020
And then the old man says,
"No, really, I'm asking.

88
00:04:56,120 --> 00:04:58,160
- Who am I?"

89
00:04:58,760 --> 00:05:00,460
I don't get it.

90
00:05:00,560 --> 00:05:02,860
"Who am I?" like, like he
forgot who he was.

91
00:05:04,040 --> 00:05:05,420
Okay, but wouldn't the joke be better

92
00:05:05,520 --> 00:05:07,620
- if the old man says...
- Okay, one...

93
00:05:07,720 --> 00:05:09,300
- What?
- ...two...

94
00:05:09,400 --> 00:05:10,900
...three!

95
00:05:12,840 --> 00:05:14,020
Aren't we graduates now?

96
00:05:14,120 --> 00:05:15,180
You do this every time!

97
00:05:15,280 --> 00:05:16,300
- Come on!
- Okay!

98
00:05:16,400 --> 00:05:18,220
One, two, three!

99
00:05:19,520 --> 00:05:20,580
There you go.

100
00:05:23,600 --> 00:05:26,148
So, I guess this is it.

101
00:05:26,520 --> 00:05:27,860
The last night of our childhood.

102
00:05:27,960 --> 00:05:29,900
I guess everything is
gonna be different.

103
00:05:30,000 --> 00:05:30,980
No.

104
00:05:31,080 --> 00:05:33,860
Tomorrow the only thing
that changes is what we do.

105
00:05:33,960 --> 00:05:35,460
It doesn't change who we are.

106
00:05:35,560 --> 00:05:36,860
Quick question: Who are we?

107
00:05:36,960 --> 00:05:37,940
Friends.

108
00:05:38,040 --> 00:05:39,380
- Friends forever.
- Yes.

109
00:05:39,480 --> 00:05:41,300
Even when you're both
assigned to be Birth Mothers.

110
00:05:41,400 --> 00:05:42,460
Hey!

111
00:05:42,560 --> 00:05:44,580
Well, I guess we'll
find out tomorrow, huh?

112
00:05:44,680 --> 00:05:46,220
<i>Citizens are reminded</i>

113
00:05:46,320 --> 00:05:49,580
<i>that evening recreation
will end in 30 minutes.</i>

114
00:05:49,680 --> 00:05:51,386
<i>Thank you.</i>

115
00:05:51,920 --> 00:05:54,340
Well, he did need
to be rehabilitated.

116
00:05:54,440 --> 00:05:57,140
And I know he was Lily's Teacher,
but what was I supposed to do?

117
00:05:59,600 --> 00:06:01,147
I feel...

118
00:06:02,480 --> 00:06:03,460
disappointment.

119
00:06:03,560 --> 00:06:04,820
What was the Elders' decision?

120
00:06:04,920 --> 00:06:06,180
Released to Elsewhere.

121
00:06:06,280 --> 00:06:08,100
Can I be "Released to
Elsewhere," Mother?

122
00:06:08,200 --> 00:06:09,620
Even just for one day?

123
00:06:09,720 --> 00:06:12,143
No, you're too young, Lily Billy.

124
00:06:14,960 --> 00:06:17,542
Jonas, your turn for Feelings.

125
00:06:19,680 --> 00:06:22,387
Well, I guess I'm sort of...

126
00:06:23,360 --> 00:06:25,021
terrified.

127
00:06:25,440 --> 00:06:27,060
Precision of language.

128
00:06:27,160 --> 00:06:29,424
I mean anxious.

129
00:06:30,640 --> 00:06:31,780
When you were about to graduate,

130
00:06:31,880 --> 00:06:35,180
did you ever feel like there
was no position meant for you?

131
00:06:35,280 --> 00:06:37,740
They've been watching since
you were a Newchild.

132
00:06:37,840 --> 00:06:39,944
The Elders are never wrong.

133
00:06:42,680 --> 00:06:44,625
You'll find your place.

134
00:06:47,840 --> 00:06:49,300
<i>Welcome, citizens,</i>

135
00:06:49,400 --> 00:06:51,780
<i>to the annual Ceremony
of Advancement.</i>

136
00:06:51,880 --> 00:06:54,587
<i>Please stand by for a transmission.</i>

137
00:06:57,560 --> 00:06:58,940
<i>Good morning, Community.</i>

138
00:06:59,040 --> 00:07:00,900
Good morning, Chief Elder.

139
00:07:01,000 --> 00:07:03,740
<i>I apologize for my remote attendance.</i>

140
00:07:03,840 --> 00:07:05,700
We accept your apology.

141
00:07:05,800 --> 00:07:09,509
<i>I can't be at every
Ceremony in person.</i>

142
00:07:10,120 --> 00:07:11,420
<i>But here's a secret:</i>

143
00:07:11,520 --> 00:07:14,261
<i>you are my favorite Community.</i>

144
00:07:15,160 --> 00:07:17,100
<i>However, because we do not lie,</i>

145
00:07:17,200 --> 00:07:19,980
<i>I readily admit I say
that to every Community.</i>

146
00:07:22,080 --> 00:07:23,700
<i>Beginnings...</i>

147
00:07:23,800 --> 00:07:25,860
<i>From disorder and chaos,</i>

148
00:07:25,960 --> 00:07:29,111
<i>from great suffering, great pain.</i>

149
00:07:29,640 --> 00:07:34,100
<i>From confusion and envy and hatred</i>

150
00:07:34,200 --> 00:07:35,980
<i>came a solution:</i>

151
00:07:36,080 --> 00:07:37,700
<i>Communities.</i>

152
00:07:37,800 --> 00:07:43,909
<i>Serene, beautiful places where
disorder became harmony.</i>

153
00:07:45,520 --> 00:07:48,260
<i>Let me get through it.</i>

154
00:07:49,960 --> 00:07:51,780
<i>Oh, fine.</i>

155
00:07:51,880 --> 00:07:53,580
<i>It begins.</i>

156
00:07:53,680 --> 00:07:55,545
<i>The Ceremony.</i>

157
00:07:56,440 --> 00:07:59,700
<i>Ceremony of the Release to Elsewhere,</i>

158
00:07:59,800 --> 00:08:03,420
<i>honoring the elderly citizens
who have devoted their work</i>

159
00:08:03,520 --> 00:08:06,740
<i>to the beauty and harmony
of our beloved Community,</i>

160
00:08:06,840 --> 00:08:10,628
<i>and are now ready for joyous
retirement to Elsewhere.</i>

161
00:08:11,800 --> 00:08:13,580
<i>Celebrating the Newchildren,</i>

162
00:08:13,680 --> 00:08:16,780
<i>proudly engineered by our
esteemed geneticists.</i>

163
00:08:16,880 --> 00:08:18,100
Abigail.

164
00:08:18,200 --> 00:08:19,980
<i>Produced by our honored
Birth Mothers...</i>

165
00:08:20,080 --> 00:08:22,180
- Aurelia.
<i>- ...these infants</i>

166
00:08:22,280 --> 00:08:24,740
<i>will now join their
assigned family units.</i>

167
00:08:24,840 --> 00:08:26,626
Caleb.

168
00:08:27,400 --> 00:08:30,500
<i>Reaching their halfway
mark towards graduation,</i>

169
00:08:30,600 --> 00:08:32,940
<i>our Nines today receive a symbol</i>

170
00:08:33,040 --> 00:08:36,460
<i>of their developing independence
and responsibility.</i>

171
00:08:39,120 --> 00:08:42,020
<i>Celebrating the graduates who, today,</i>

172
00:08:42,120 --> 00:08:45,140
<i>will be assigned their
positions in our Community.</i>

173
00:08:45,240 --> 00:08:46,220
Good luck.

174
00:08:46,320 --> 00:08:47,300
You, too.

175
00:08:47,400 --> 00:08:50,420
<i>All of your training has been</i>

176
00:08:50,520 --> 00:08:52,540
<i>to help you fit in,</i>

177
00:08:52,640 --> 00:08:56,340
<i>to curb any impulse that may
set you apart from others,</i>

178
00:08:56,440 --> 00:09:00,300
<i>but today, we honor your differences,</i>

179
00:09:00,400 --> 00:09:03,060
<i>for they have determined your future.</i>

180
00:09:03,160 --> 00:09:05,940
<i>Here are the Leaders and the Teachers</i>

181
00:09:06,040 --> 00:09:09,700
<i>and the Workers and Birth
Mothers of tomorrow,</i>

182
00:09:09,800 --> 00:09:12,940
<i>and I think we're in very good hands.</i>

183
00:09:13,040 --> 00:09:16,430
<i>Number one, Madeline.</i>

184
00:09:16,760 --> 00:09:18,380
<i>Birth Mother.</i>

185
00:09:18,480 --> 00:09:20,340
<i>Thank you for your childhood.</i>

186
00:09:20,440 --> 00:09:22,420
<i>Number two, Ross.</i>

187
00:09:22,520 --> 00:09:24,431
<i>Instructor of the Middles.</i>

188
00:09:24,880 --> 00:09:26,540
<i>Thank you for your childhood.</i>

189
00:09:26,640 --> 00:09:29,188
<i>Number 51, Asher.</i>

190
00:09:30,400 --> 00:09:32,620
<i>Unruly, careless.</i>

191
00:09:32,720 --> 00:09:36,180
<i>Sometimes those most in
need of responsibility</i>

192
00:09:36,280 --> 00:09:39,670
<i>learn best by being the
practitioners of it.</i>

193
00:09:39,920 --> 00:09:42,184
<i>Drone Pilot.</i>

194
00:09:43,080 --> 00:09:44,500
<i>Thank you for your childhood.</i>

195
00:09:44,600 --> 00:09:45,820
You can keep it!

196
00:09:48,120 --> 00:09:49,906
Thanks!

197
00:09:50,920 --> 00:09:54,981
<i>Number 53, Ayanda.</i>

198
00:09:55,120 --> 00:09:56,820
<i>Recreation Leader.</i>

199
00:09:56,920 --> 00:09:59,140
<i>Thank you for your childhood.</i>

200
00:09:59,240 --> 00:10:02,140
<i>Number 54, Kathy.</i>

201
00:10:02,240 --> 00:10:04,020
They skipped Jonas.

202
00:10:04,120 --> 00:10:05,660
<i>Thank you for your childhood.</i>

203
00:10:05,760 --> 00:10:06,860
<i>Number 78, Lloyd.</i>

204
00:10:06,960 --> 00:10:08,340
<i>Geneticist.</i>

205
00:10:08,440 --> 00:10:09,740
<i>Thank you for your childhood.</i>

206
00:10:09,840 --> 00:10:11,580
<i>Number 83, Yara.</i>

207
00:10:13,520 --> 00:10:15,500
<i>Number 96, Chris.</i>

208
00:10:15,600 --> 00:10:16,620
<i>Food maintenance.</i>

209
00:10:16,720 --> 00:10:18,380
<i>Number 100, Quinn.</i>

210
00:10:18,480 --> 00:10:19,740
<i>Caretaker of the Old.</i>

211
00:10:19,840 --> 00:10:22,380
<i>Number 104, Fiona.</i>

212
00:10:22,480 --> 00:10:23,700
<i>From the beginning,</i>

213
00:10:23,800 --> 00:10:27,260
<i>it was clear Fiona flourished
working with Newchildren.</i>

214
00:10:27,360 --> 00:10:28,420
<i>Fiona...</i>

215
00:10:28,520 --> 00:10:30,060
<i>Nurturer.</i>

216
00:10:30,160 --> 00:10:32,424
<i>Thank you for your childhood.</i>

217
00:10:33,920 --> 00:10:36,300
<i>Number 105, Lucia.</i>

218
00:10:36,400 --> 00:10:38,540
<i>Instructor of the Twelves.</i>

219
00:10:38,640 --> 00:10:40,820
<i>Number 120, Jack.</i>

220
00:10:40,920 --> 00:10:42,300
<i>Department of Justice...</i>

221
00:10:42,400 --> 00:10:43,700
<i>Assistant.</i>

222
00:10:43,800 --> 00:10:45,580
<i>...Nutrition Technician.</i>

223
00:10:45,680 --> 00:10:47,220
<i>Thank you for your childhood.</i>

224
00:10:47,320 --> 00:10:50,630
<i>Number 150, Pierre.</i>

225
00:10:51,400 --> 00:10:53,550
<i>Groundskeeper.</i>

226
00:10:53,880 --> 00:10:56,621
<i>Thank you for your childhood.</i>

227
00:11:03,440 --> 00:11:05,500
<i>You feel I have made a mistake.</i>

228
00:11:05,600 --> 00:11:07,980
<i>I apologize to my Community.</i>

229
00:11:08,080 --> 00:11:10,380
We accept your apology.

230
00:11:10,480 --> 00:11:13,790
<i>Number 52, please step forward.</i>

231
00:11:15,600 --> 00:11:17,700
<i>Jonas has not been
assigned a position.</i>

232
00:11:17,800 --> 00:11:19,700
<i>Jonas has been selected.</i>

233
00:11:19,800 --> 00:11:24,350
<i>We were not hasty this time.
We could not afford another failure.</i>

234
00:11:25,960 --> 00:11:29,540
<i>Jonas possesses all four attributes:</i>

235
00:11:29,640 --> 00:11:32,540
<i>intelligence, integrity, courage,</i>

236
00:11:32,640 --> 00:11:35,980
<i>and one I can name,
but I cannot describe</i>

237
00:11:36,080 --> 00:11:38,700
<i>the capacity to see beyond.</i>

238
00:11:38,800 --> 00:11:42,782
<i>But I must warn you,
your training involves pain.</i>

239
00:11:42,960 --> 00:11:46,304
<i>Pain far beyond anything we know.</i>

240
00:11:46,640 --> 00:11:48,630
<i>Are you strong enough?</i>

241
00:11:48,800 --> 00:11:50,780
<i>Do we think Jonas is brave enough?</i>

242
00:11:56,480 --> 00:11:58,820
<i>Jonas, you have been selected</i>

243
00:11:58,920 --> 00:12:01,700
<i>as our next Receiver of Memory.</i>

244
00:12:01,800 --> 00:12:04,223
<i>Thank you for your childhood.</i>

245
00:12:05,520 --> 00:12:06,780
<i>Jonas...</i>

246
00:12:06,880 --> 00:12:09,780
Jonas. Jonas. Jonas. Jonas.

247
00:12:09,880 --> 00:12:15,260
Jonas. Jonas. Jonas. Jonas.
Jonas. Jonas. Jonas.

248
00:12:15,360 --> 00:12:18,940
Jonas. Jonas. Jonas. Jonas. Jonas.

249
00:12:35,800 --> 00:12:37,940
- Help me up, please.
- Okay, this foot, yeah.

250
00:12:38,040 --> 00:12:39,300
That one, you got it.

251
00:12:39,400 --> 00:12:40,380
Sit back, sit back.

252
00:12:40,480 --> 00:12:42,060
Is Jonas now more powerful than you?

253
00:12:42,160 --> 00:12:43,860
- Shh.
- What did the Chief Elder mean

254
00:12:43,960 --> 00:12:46,340
when she said, "We cannot
afford another failure"?

255
00:12:46,440 --> 00:12:48,260
Well, ten years ago, the Receiver...

256
00:12:48,360 --> 00:12:49,780
We do not speak of it.

257
00:12:49,880 --> 00:12:51,780
You've been greatly honored.

258
00:12:51,880 --> 00:12:53,780
You've got it! Go, go, go!
You've got it, got it, got it!

259
00:12:53,880 --> 00:12:55,820
- I can do it.
- I should probably catch Lily.

260
00:12:55,920 --> 00:12:57,900
- Good!
- I can ride!

261
00:12:58,000 --> 00:12:59,865
Good, Lily!

262
00:13:01,080 --> 00:13:03,060
<i>Receiver of Memory.</i>

263
00:13:03,160 --> 00:13:05,025
<i>Five rules.</i>

264
00:13:05,160 --> 00:13:08,260
<i>One: Report directly to
the Receiver of Memory</i>

265
00:13:08,360 --> 00:13:10,100
<i>for your training.</i>

266
00:13:10,200 --> 00:13:13,590
<i>After training, return
immediately to your dwelling.</i>

267
00:13:14,800 --> 00:13:16,940
<i>Two: From this moment,</i>

268
00:13:17,040 --> 00:13:20,700
<i>you are exempt from all
rules governing rudeness.</i>

269
00:13:20,800 --> 00:13:22,950
<i>You may ask any question.</i>

270
00:13:23,160 --> 00:13:25,700
<i>Three: Aside from
your daily injection,</i>

271
00:13:25,800 --> 00:13:27,940
<i>you may not receive other medicines,</i>

272
00:13:28,040 --> 00:13:29,900
<i>especially those for pain.</i>

273
00:13:30,000 --> 00:13:33,868
<i>Injected. S-7- 5- 2.</i>

274
00:13:34,040 --> 00:13:38,784
<i>Four: You may not discuss
your training with anyone.</i>

275
00:13:40,440 --> 00:13:41,740
<i>Ever.</i>

276
00:13:41,840 --> 00:13:43,260
Yours look so important.

277
00:13:43,360 --> 00:13:45,340
I don't know. I stick out.

278
00:13:45,440 --> 00:13:48,060
Well, yeah, there's only
one Receiver of Memory.

279
00:13:48,160 --> 00:13:49,140
Two.

280
00:13:49,240 --> 00:13:50,340
What did they say again?

281
00:13:50,440 --> 00:13:52,700
You have the capacity to see beyond?

282
00:13:52,800 --> 00:13:54,301
Yeah.

283
00:13:54,520 --> 00:13:56,749
Can't wait to hear
every single detail.

284
00:13:57,040 --> 00:14:00,669
<i>Five: You may lie.</i>

285
00:14:05,920 --> 00:14:08,100
<i>Asher and I, we used
to dare each other</i>

286
00:14:08,200 --> 00:14:10,140
<i>to get close to his place.</i>

287
00:14:10,240 --> 00:14:13,027
<i>It was built right on the Edge.</i>

288
00:14:13,760 --> 00:14:16,060
<i>We'd all heard of people
getting lost to the Edge,</i>

289
00:14:16,160 --> 00:14:18,420
<i>never to be seen again.</i>

290
00:14:18,520 --> 00:14:20,670
<i>And yet, here I was,</i>

291
00:14:21,320 --> 00:14:24,220
<i>being told that I'd have to
get close to it every day,</i>

292
00:14:24,320 --> 00:14:26,822
<i>for the rest of my life.</i>

293
00:14:38,040 --> 00:14:39,780
<i>Welcome.</i>

294
00:14:40,320 --> 00:14:42,140
Hi.

295
00:14:42,240 --> 00:14:45,061
- I'm Jonas. I'm...
<i>- Please gaze at the sensor.</i>

296
00:14:47,240 --> 00:14:50,027
<i>Welcome, Receiver of Memory.</i>

297
00:15:35,680 --> 00:15:38,020
They're called books.

298
00:15:38,120 --> 00:15:39,260
Your books.

299
00:15:39,360 --> 00:15:41,780
- My name is...
- I know who you are.

300
00:15:41,880 --> 00:15:42,900
Of course.

301
00:15:43,000 --> 00:15:44,180
I apologize.

302
00:15:47,480 --> 00:15:49,311
I apologize.

303
00:15:49,880 --> 00:15:51,825
Don't say that.

304
00:15:52,600 --> 00:15:54,100
"I apologize."

305
00:15:54,200 --> 00:15:57,580
Don't apologize to me ever again.

306
00:15:57,680 --> 00:15:59,750
Not here.

307
00:16:01,120 --> 00:16:02,900
We haven't the time.

308
00:16:03,000 --> 00:16:04,300
"I apologize."

309
00:16:04,400 --> 00:16:06,740
That's an automatic pleasantry.

310
00:16:06,840 --> 00:16:08,300
It doesn't mean anything.

311
00:16:08,400 --> 00:16:09,900
I apologize. I'm sorry.

312
00:16:10,000 --> 00:16:11,831
I mean...

313
00:16:11,960 --> 00:16:14,747
We are here for only one purpose.

314
00:16:16,000 --> 00:16:20,661
Simply stated, although it
isn't really simple at all,

315
00:16:20,920 --> 00:16:25,100
I will transmit to you all the
memories that I hold within me.

316
00:16:25,200 --> 00:16:27,180
Memories of the past.

317
00:16:27,280 --> 00:16:30,020
I would be very interested
to learn about your life.

318
00:16:30,120 --> 00:16:32,622
No, no. Not...

319
00:16:32,960 --> 00:16:34,791
Not my life.

320
00:16:35,080 --> 00:16:37,620
You will learn the secret
history of the world.

321
00:16:37,720 --> 00:16:39,820
Before me, before you, generations...

322
00:16:39,920 --> 00:16:41,831
Back and back and back.

323
00:16:42,160 --> 00:16:44,620
When things were different,
when there was more.

324
00:16:44,720 --> 00:16:46,060
More?

325
00:16:46,160 --> 00:16:48,060
The chair.

326
00:16:48,160 --> 00:16:52,660
You see, no one in our Community
has any memory of the past.

327
00:16:52,760 --> 00:16:54,420
Only me.

328
00:16:54,520 --> 00:16:57,300
When the... Elders need
guidance on matters that are

329
00:16:57,400 --> 00:17:00,340
beyond their experience,
I provide wisdom.

330
00:17:00,440 --> 00:17:01,980
That is now your role.

331
00:17:02,080 --> 00:17:06,180
To provide guidance in the present
using memories of the past.

332
00:17:06,280 --> 00:17:08,384
Move closer.

333
00:17:12,680 --> 00:17:14,670
Where to begin?

334
00:17:16,760 --> 00:17:18,750
Move closer.

335
00:17:21,480 --> 00:17:22,947
Closer.

336
00:17:26,360 --> 00:17:29,300
There is no way for me to prepare you

337
00:17:29,400 --> 00:17:31,540
for what I'm going to do now.

338
00:17:31,640 --> 00:17:33,983
You can take comfort in knowing

339
00:17:34,560 --> 00:17:37,540
you are completely helpless.

340
00:17:47,320 --> 00:17:51,420
If any of this proves too much
for you, tell me immediately.

341
00:17:51,520 --> 00:17:53,704
I just have...

342
00:19:22,280 --> 00:19:26,660
<i>♪ Holy night</i>

343
00:19:26,760 --> 00:19:27,860
<i>♪ All ♪</i>

344
00:19:31,480 --> 00:19:32,500
That was...

345
00:19:32,600 --> 00:19:33,940
It was...

346
00:19:34,040 --> 00:19:35,020
How did that happen?

347
00:19:35,120 --> 00:19:37,900
What do you mean, how? It happened.

348
00:19:38,000 --> 00:19:39,220
But it's impossible.

349
00:19:39,320 --> 00:19:40,380
And yet, it happened.

350
00:19:40,480 --> 00:19:42,311
Well, why?

351
00:19:42,720 --> 00:19:44,020
Why don't we have...

352
00:19:44,120 --> 00:19:45,621
Th...

353
00:19:46,360 --> 00:19:48,191
That thing?

354
00:19:48,320 --> 00:19:51,180
Go on. The memories,
they give you the word.

355
00:19:51,280 --> 00:19:52,500
It's not a "thing." It's...

356
00:19:52,600 --> 00:19:54,420
- Sled.
- Sled.

357
00:19:54,520 --> 00:19:55,980
And the...

358
00:19:57,640 --> 00:19:59,630
- Snow.
- Snow.

359
00:19:59,960 --> 00:20:01,500
Did my parents have them? Did you?

360
00:20:01,600 --> 00:20:04,580
No, no. It's a very distant memory.

361
00:20:04,680 --> 00:20:09,746
Simply stated, there is no snow
because of climate control.

362
00:20:10,440 --> 00:20:12,540
But why don't people know about them?

363
00:20:12,640 --> 00:20:15,140
I mean, what's so dangerous
about the memory of a sled?

364
00:20:15,240 --> 00:20:17,460
What's so dangerous?

365
00:20:17,560 --> 00:20:21,020
For a sled, you need snow.

366
00:20:21,120 --> 00:20:22,140
Snow is cold.

367
00:20:22,240 --> 00:20:24,549
Cold destroys crops.

368
00:20:24,760 --> 00:20:27,220
Which meant farmers couldn't farm.

369
00:20:27,320 --> 00:20:30,780
Unpredictable weather,
hills, mountains,

370
00:20:30,880 --> 00:20:33,660
made it difficult to transport food.

371
00:20:33,760 --> 00:20:37,300
Then we had hunger,
starvation, famine.

372
00:20:37,400 --> 00:20:40,551
Everything is connected,
everything is a balance.

373
00:20:41,240 --> 00:20:43,300
With good there is always bad.

374
00:20:43,400 --> 00:20:45,504
- The two...
- Show me more.

375
00:20:48,600 --> 00:20:50,590
Let's go for a walk.

376
00:20:52,680 --> 00:20:55,421
A real one, with your legs.

377
00:20:55,960 --> 00:20:59,304
At the bottom of the hill,
I saw something.

378
00:21:00,040 --> 00:21:01,905
Like a place.

379
00:21:03,160 --> 00:21:04,740
- Home.
- Home. Yes.

380
00:21:04,840 --> 00:21:06,260
Home? Like a dwelling?

381
00:21:06,360 --> 00:21:07,660
- Receiver.
- Afternoon.

382
00:21:07,760 --> 00:21:10,706
No. It is different.

383
00:21:10,920 --> 00:21:13,707
A dwelling is not a home.

384
00:21:14,200 --> 00:21:16,509
A home is more.

385
00:21:18,680 --> 00:21:21,220
Your instructions said I can lie.

386
00:21:21,320 --> 00:21:22,380
Do you lie?

387
00:21:22,480 --> 00:21:24,500
All the time.

388
00:21:24,600 --> 00:21:27,102
Mostly for personal amusement.

389
00:21:27,760 --> 00:21:30,060
But I won't lie to you.

390
00:21:30,160 --> 00:21:32,583
How do I know that's not a lie?

391
00:21:37,280 --> 00:21:39,430
There was someone else before me.

392
00:21:40,080 --> 00:21:42,070
What happened to them?

393
00:21:47,280 --> 00:21:49,180
One more question.

394
00:21:49,280 --> 00:21:51,700
If I'm now the Receiver,
what does that make you?

395
00:21:51,800 --> 00:21:54,951
Well, then that must make me...

396
00:21:55,120 --> 00:21:57,270
The Giver.

397
00:22:06,040 --> 00:22:07,780
So, how was it?

398
00:22:08,280 --> 00:22:09,620
It was good.

399
00:22:09,720 --> 00:22:11,426
What'd you do?

400
00:22:12,800 --> 00:22:14,140
We just talked.

401
00:22:14,240 --> 00:22:16,105
What else?

402
00:22:16,960 --> 00:22:18,220
That's it.

403
00:22:18,320 --> 00:22:20,460
- You seem different.
- How do you mean?

404
00:22:22,080 --> 00:22:23,460
He can't settle down,

405
00:22:23,560 --> 00:22:25,420
no matter what I do.

406
00:22:25,520 --> 00:22:27,380
And you said you'd look after him.

407
00:22:27,480 --> 00:22:29,860
- I know, I know.
- I apologize.

408
00:22:29,960 --> 00:22:31,820
I accept your apology.

409
00:22:31,920 --> 00:22:33,500
- Thank you, Dinah.
- Thank you.

410
00:22:33,600 --> 00:22:35,100
Hey.

411
00:22:38,240 --> 00:22:39,260
Gabriel?

412
00:22:39,360 --> 00:22:41,460
How does Jonas know the child's name?

413
00:22:41,560 --> 00:22:43,340
Jonas met Gabriel the other day.

414
00:22:43,440 --> 00:22:45,863
Look at him! He's so cute!

415
00:22:46,360 --> 00:22:47,540
- Hello. Hi.
- Would you like

416
00:22:47,640 --> 00:22:49,824
to issue me a warning,
Director of Justice?

417
00:22:49,960 --> 00:22:51,620
It's just for a while, Mother.

418
00:22:51,720 --> 00:22:53,300
Till the little guy catches up.

419
00:22:53,400 --> 00:22:56,551
I think we're all in agreement
that he sleeps in my room.

420
00:22:56,840 --> 00:22:58,780
Only if the Elders say it's okay.

421
00:22:58,880 --> 00:23:00,666
They will.

422
00:23:00,840 --> 00:23:03,946
Yeah. Lily, give me
your Comfort Object.

423
00:23:05,200 --> 00:23:07,623
Come on, Lily. It's time for bed.

424
00:23:07,960 --> 00:23:10,462
- Look at this.
- Bye, baby.

425
00:23:11,040 --> 00:23:14,020
This is a mythical
creature called a hippo.

426
00:23:14,120 --> 00:23:17,900
And it's incredibly fast,
because it has two, three, four,

427
00:23:18,000 --> 00:23:20,502
five legs.

428
00:23:21,280 --> 00:23:23,460
<i>We had the same mark.</i>

429
00:23:23,560 --> 00:23:26,222
<i>I almost didn't need
to see his to know.</i>

430
00:23:26,720 --> 00:23:27,820
<i>But I felt it.</i>

431
00:23:27,920 --> 00:23:30,500
<i>Felt that one day,</i>

432
00:23:30,600 --> 00:23:32,260
<i>Gabriel would be chosen, too.</i>

433
00:23:32,360 --> 00:23:33,700
A hippo, Gabe.

434
00:23:35,600 --> 00:23:37,306
Yeah.

435
00:23:48,720 --> 00:23:50,460
That's the pain they all talk about.

436
00:23:50,560 --> 00:23:53,660
No. Not even close. Did you...

437
00:23:53,760 --> 00:23:56,140
It had a face.

438
00:23:56,240 --> 00:23:58,260
Wait, was that thing alive?

439
00:23:58,360 --> 00:23:59,380
Don't skip ahead.

440
00:23:59,480 --> 00:24:01,100
Did you notice anything about it?

441
00:24:01,200 --> 00:24:02,340
Yes. It hurt.

442
00:24:02,440 --> 00:24:04,783
No. Any quality?

443
00:24:07,040 --> 00:24:09,065
Well, maybe.

444
00:24:09,200 --> 00:24:12,067
I think I saw it in my
friend Fiona's hair.

445
00:24:13,880 --> 00:24:16,303
My first was yellow.

446
00:24:16,600 --> 00:24:19,421
If you thought the
sled was special...

447
00:25:04,800 --> 00:25:07,109
Oh, whoa!

448
00:25:10,120 --> 00:25:11,860
It's...

449
00:25:13,800 --> 00:25:15,506
red.

450
00:25:15,920 --> 00:25:18,263
- Just like her hair.
- Yes.

451
00:25:18,680 --> 00:25:22,468
There's red, green, blue,
many different colors.

452
00:25:22,800 --> 00:25:25,382
You'll see them all in time.

453
00:25:26,040 --> 00:25:30,784
When our people, they chose
to do away with all of them,

454
00:25:31,120 --> 00:25:35,545
color, race, religion,
they created Sameness.

455
00:25:36,080 --> 00:25:38,821
If we were different,
we could be envious,

456
00:25:39,680 --> 00:25:44,469
angry, or resentful,
consumed with hatred.

457
00:25:46,160 --> 00:25:48,424
We need Sameness.

458
00:25:48,720 --> 00:25:49,740
Don't you think?

459
00:25:49,840 --> 00:25:52,024
Oh, I completely agree.

460
00:25:52,680 --> 00:25:54,545
But still...

461
00:25:54,960 --> 00:25:59,184
It's all so beautiful.

462
00:26:04,400 --> 00:26:07,380
<i>They'd always said
Elsewhere was so far away,</i>

463
00:26:08,200 --> 00:26:10,180
<i>but it wasn't.</i>

464
00:26:10,280 --> 00:26:12,066
<i>It was right there.</i>

465
00:26:13,840 --> 00:26:15,626
<i>Close enough to touch.</i>

466
00:26:16,600 --> 00:26:18,020
Jonas?

467
00:26:18,120 --> 00:26:19,740
Have you fallen?

468
00:26:19,840 --> 00:26:21,420
Do you need immediate help?

469
00:26:21,520 --> 00:26:23,541
No. I was just...

470
00:26:24,640 --> 00:26:26,585
What's going on with you?

471
00:26:26,800 --> 00:26:28,060
Nothing is going on with me.

472
00:26:28,160 --> 00:26:29,980
No, you're right, it's totally normal

473
00:26:30,080 --> 00:26:31,500
to lie in the grass
and stare at the sky.

474
00:26:31,600 --> 00:26:33,909
No, I was just...

475
00:26:35,120 --> 00:26:37,622
You're seeing something, aren't you?

476
00:26:41,920 --> 00:26:44,309
Can't you tell me?

477
00:26:50,400 --> 00:26:52,231
Give me your hands.

478
00:27:06,080 --> 00:27:07,945
What do you see?

479
00:27:10,160 --> 00:27:12,469
- Oh, my goodness.
- You see it?

480
00:27:13,000 --> 00:27:14,740
Yes.

481
00:27:15,640 --> 00:27:17,471
It's water.

482
00:27:17,680 --> 00:27:19,670
No, come on, concentrate.

483
00:27:25,320 --> 00:27:28,107
Hi.

484
00:27:28,320 --> 00:27:31,340
Jonas was just teaching
me about his training.

485
00:27:31,440 --> 00:27:33,460
As you can see,
it's incredibly interesting.

486
00:27:33,560 --> 00:27:35,620
Can't be half as great as mine.

487
00:27:35,720 --> 00:27:37,949
Care to have your minds blown?

488
00:27:41,440 --> 00:27:42,420
Whoa!

489
00:27:42,520 --> 00:27:44,020
Do you know how to fly those?

490
00:27:44,120 --> 00:27:45,380
Absolutely.

491
00:27:45,480 --> 00:27:46,900
Sort of.

492
00:27:47,000 --> 00:27:49,229
I'm learning.

493
00:27:50,280 --> 00:27:53,511
When I'm flying,
looking down at everything,

494
00:27:54,360 --> 00:27:56,780
it's like I'm seeing things
for the very first time.

495
00:27:56,880 --> 00:27:58,660
You get to fly into Elsewhere?

496
00:27:58,760 --> 00:27:59,740
Oh, yeah.

497
00:27:59,840 --> 00:28:02,149
Once, when I was
looking at that mist,

498
00:28:02,560 --> 00:28:05,660
even though they tell us there's
nothing close to the Edge,

499
00:28:05,760 --> 00:28:08,547
I thought I saw a tree
out there somewhere.

500
00:28:10,240 --> 00:28:11,700
Well, don't get too excited.

501
00:28:11,800 --> 00:28:13,740
I've actually seen Elsewhere.

502
00:28:13,840 --> 00:28:17,620
It's just mostly our farms,
weird rocks, that kind of stuff.

503
00:28:17,720 --> 00:28:19,660
What's weird about them?

504
00:28:19,760 --> 00:28:21,944
There's these two huge rocks

505
00:28:22,320 --> 00:28:26,900
leaning against each other,
making a kind of triangle.

506
00:28:27,000 --> 00:28:28,660
Hey, it's kind of like our triangle.

507
00:28:28,760 --> 00:28:29,780
What's past there?

508
00:28:29,880 --> 00:28:31,220
Don't know.

509
00:28:31,320 --> 00:28:33,663
We're not allowed to fly past that.

510
00:28:35,080 --> 00:28:37,180
So many secrets.

511
00:28:37,280 --> 00:28:39,580
So what are your secrets?

512
00:28:39,680 --> 00:28:40,780
Uh, nothing.

513
00:28:40,880 --> 00:28:42,660
What do you mean, "Uh, nothing"?

514
00:28:42,760 --> 00:28:44,625
You're Receiver of Memory.

515
00:28:48,880 --> 00:28:50,711
Maybe I can show you.

516
00:28:51,360 --> 00:28:53,900
- Okay, grab a tray.
- What?

517
00:28:54,000 --> 00:28:56,548
Bring it over to the
solar panel. Come on.

518
00:28:56,920 --> 00:28:59,946
Now this might seem a little funny,
but you got to trust me.

519
00:29:01,640 --> 00:29:03,744
Okay, sit down on the tray.

520
00:29:05,240 --> 00:29:06,940
- Careful.
- You're not gonna...

521
00:29:07,040 --> 00:29:09,900
- What, you're scared?
- I'm scared of nothing.

522
00:29:10,000 --> 00:29:11,740
I don't know, it's just...

523
00:29:11,840 --> 00:29:13,260
It's against the rules, Jonas.

524
00:29:13,360 --> 00:29:16,181
Since when do you
care about the rules?

525
00:29:18,240 --> 00:29:20,708
Actually, I have auxiliary training.

526
00:29:20,880 --> 00:29:22,791
I'll see you guys.

527
00:29:24,480 --> 00:29:28,302
Look who grew up,
but lucky for you, I haven't.

528
00:29:34,480 --> 00:29:35,780
Okay?

529
00:29:35,880 --> 00:29:36,940
Now, go!

530
00:30:05,080 --> 00:30:07,344
Put your heels down to slow it!

531
00:30:22,280 --> 00:30:23,860
I think your training might be a bit

532
00:30:23,960 --> 00:30:25,900
- more fun than mine.
<i>- Please stand by</i>

533
00:30:26,000 --> 00:30:27,980
<i>for a Community announcement.</i>

534
00:30:28,080 --> 00:30:30,660
<i>Citizens are reminded that
it is impolite to touch</i>

535
00:30:30,760 --> 00:30:33,460
<i>community members outside
your family unit.</i>

536
00:30:33,560 --> 00:30:35,300
<i>Thank you.</i>

537
00:30:38,520 --> 00:30:40,140
<i>He's punctual.</i>

538
00:30:40,240 --> 00:30:43,020
- He's inquisitive.
- How inquisitive?

539
00:30:43,120 --> 00:30:45,180
He's interested in his position.

540
00:30:45,280 --> 00:30:47,544
Then why is he breaking the rules?

541
00:30:48,200 --> 00:30:50,900
He has been observed
trying to share his training

542
00:30:51,000 --> 00:30:52,540
with his former classmates.

543
00:30:52,640 --> 00:30:54,744
That always happens.

544
00:30:55,560 --> 00:30:58,267
But it's an impossible experiment.

545
00:30:58,520 --> 00:31:02,670
Even I tried to share the memories
back when I was in training...

546
00:31:03,120 --> 00:31:04,985
If you remember.

547
00:31:05,520 --> 00:31:08,711
So, forget about it.

548
00:31:09,560 --> 00:31:13,220
I don't tell you what to do in
your position, so don't tell me.

549
00:31:13,320 --> 00:31:17,420
I apologize, but isn't
that what's happening now?

550
00:31:17,520 --> 00:31:21,502
Your apology is accepted,
but you are being careless.

551
00:31:21,920 --> 00:31:23,340
You're moving too fast.

552
00:31:23,440 --> 00:31:26,546
We both know what happened
ten years ago with the girl.

553
00:31:26,800 --> 00:31:30,110
The girl had a name.

554
00:31:32,280 --> 00:31:34,862
You think I don't remember her name?

555
00:31:35,440 --> 00:31:37,749
I know you feel her loss.

556
00:31:48,840 --> 00:31:52,184
The boy must hold in the pain.

557
00:31:54,240 --> 00:31:56,390
Don't fail us again.

558
00:32:07,240 --> 00:32:08,980
You want me to read all these?

559
00:32:10,400 --> 00:32:11,620
What's this?

560
00:32:11,720 --> 00:32:13,940
"One day you shall meet a boy

561
00:32:14,040 --> 00:32:16,827
who answers to the name of Jonas."

562
00:32:17,480 --> 00:32:20,340
"He shall be the most powerful
of all the Receivers."

563
00:32:20,440 --> 00:32:21,660
Wait. That says...

564
00:32:21,760 --> 00:32:23,750
Don't be gullible.

565
00:32:29,920 --> 00:32:31,180
Another trick?

566
00:32:31,280 --> 00:32:33,225
Actually, no.

567
00:32:35,640 --> 00:32:38,700
It's some kind of map.

568
00:32:38,800 --> 00:32:39,900
The Triangle of Rocks!

569
00:32:40,000 --> 00:32:42,582
Hey, that's real,
my friend Asher saw it.

570
00:32:42,840 --> 00:32:44,785
Look at all these towers.

571
00:32:44,920 --> 00:32:45,940
What were they for?

572
00:32:46,040 --> 00:32:48,420
How did your friend see
the Triangle of Rocks?

573
00:32:48,520 --> 00:32:51,500
He's a pilot. He told me he saw it.

574
00:32:52,040 --> 00:32:53,541
What's past there?

575
00:32:56,400 --> 00:32:58,709
A mystery.

576
00:32:58,960 --> 00:33:00,740
"Boundary of Memory"?
Is that what they built

577
00:33:00,840 --> 00:33:03,220
so the memories would only
stay within you and me?

578
00:33:03,320 --> 00:33:04,420
Let's move on.

579
00:33:04,520 --> 00:33:05,700
Wait.

580
00:33:05,800 --> 00:33:08,020
That boundary is meant
to keep memories in.

581
00:33:08,120 --> 00:33:10,031
So if a Receiver crosses it,

582
00:33:10,240 --> 00:33:12,583
does that mean the
memories get set free?

583
00:33:13,400 --> 00:33:14,500
Perhaps.

584
00:33:14,600 --> 00:33:17,020
Perhaps if you or I crossed it,

585
00:33:17,120 --> 00:33:19,861
everyone could feel
those memories again.

586
00:33:20,640 --> 00:33:23,142
So, what am I seeing today?

587
00:33:24,360 --> 00:33:26,544
Nothing.

588
00:33:27,600 --> 00:33:30,671
You're seeing nothing today.

589
00:33:37,160 --> 00:33:39,708
We've already covered
"seeing beyond."

590
00:33:40,640 --> 00:33:43,460
There is also such a thing
as "hearing beyond."

591
00:33:43,560 --> 00:33:45,100
A table?

592
00:33:45,200 --> 00:33:47,828
All the food would
slide to the floor.

593
00:33:50,360 --> 00:33:53,380
Now, don't judge me.

594
00:33:53,480 --> 00:33:55,903
I'm not very good,

595
00:33:56,200 --> 00:33:59,180
even though I had
a very good Teacher.

596
00:34:10,400 --> 00:34:11,860
Music.

597
00:34:13,600 --> 00:34:16,620
Well, music when I
hit the right keys.

598
00:34:35,840 --> 00:34:37,990
Just like music,

599
00:34:38,280 --> 00:34:41,147
there's something else you
can't see with your eyes.

600
00:34:41,600 --> 00:34:45,547
Something that lives deep inside you.

601
00:34:45,720 --> 00:34:50,464
Something those morning
injections take away.

602
00:34:50,760 --> 00:34:53,500
But I thought the injections
are for our health.

603
00:34:53,600 --> 00:34:55,740
No, they remove something.

604
00:34:55,840 --> 00:34:57,466
What?

605
00:34:57,920 --> 00:34:59,300
Emotions.

606
00:35:01,760 --> 00:35:03,705
You mean like feelings?

607
00:35:05,120 --> 00:35:07,980
Feelings are just fleeting.

608
00:35:08,080 --> 00:35:09,706
On the surface.

609
00:35:10,560 --> 00:35:12,500
But emotions,

610
00:35:12,600 --> 00:35:15,460
they're very deep, primal.

611
00:35:15,560 --> 00:35:17,471
They linger.

612
00:35:18,880 --> 00:35:20,711
Now, Jonas...

613
00:35:21,720 --> 00:35:25,380
you might not understand where
you are or what's happening,

614
00:35:25,480 --> 00:35:28,221
but don't think about
what you're seeing.

615
00:35:28,680 --> 00:35:30,625
Listen.

616
00:35:32,280 --> 00:35:35,465
Listen to what's calling from inside.

617
00:35:49,640 --> 00:35:51,660
A beautiful wedding!

618
00:36:21,040 --> 00:36:23,500
Why would anyone want
to get rid of this?

619
00:36:23,600 --> 00:36:25,670
Good question.

620
00:36:31,400 --> 00:36:32,660
What are you doing?

621
00:36:32,760 --> 00:36:34,546
Take my hand.

622
00:36:34,680 --> 00:36:35,780
Ready?

623
00:36:38,800 --> 00:36:39,940
You ready for the fast part?

624
00:36:44,680 --> 00:36:45,660
And turn!

625
00:36:45,760 --> 00:36:46,740
Spin!

626
00:36:46,840 --> 00:36:48,460
What are you doing with her?

627
00:36:48,560 --> 00:36:50,780
Jonas says it's called dancing.

628
00:36:53,040 --> 00:36:56,066
<i>Please stand by for a transmission.</i>

629
00:36:57,720 --> 00:36:59,900
<i>I apologize for my intrusion.</i>

630
00:37:00,000 --> 00:37:01,900
We accept your apology.

631
00:37:02,000 --> 00:37:04,540
<i>I just wanted to say hello.</i>

632
00:37:04,640 --> 00:37:06,180
Hello.

633
00:37:06,280 --> 00:37:07,500
I'm Lily.

634
00:37:07,600 --> 00:37:08,980
<i>Yes, I know.</i>

635
00:37:09,080 --> 00:37:10,580
<i>You're a Nine now, isn't that right?</i>

636
00:37:11,840 --> 00:37:15,060
Lily, I think it's time for school.

637
00:37:15,160 --> 00:37:17,788
- We should probably get going.
- Hello, Jonas.

638
00:37:18,320 --> 00:37:19,300
Hello.

639
00:37:19,400 --> 00:37:20,580
<i>How is your training?</i>

640
00:37:20,680 --> 00:37:21,820
<i>Injected.</i>

641
00:37:21,920 --> 00:37:23,020
Fine.

642
00:37:23,120 --> 00:37:25,100
<i>I am concerned about the Receiver.</i>

643
00:37:25,200 --> 00:37:26,700
<i>Injected.</i>

644
00:37:26,800 --> 00:37:28,860
<i>Many years ago,
there was an incident.</i>

645
00:37:28,960 --> 00:37:30,580
What kind of incident?

646
00:37:30,680 --> 00:37:36,140
<i>Living alone in a building on
the Edge can isolate a person.</i>

647
00:37:36,240 --> 00:37:40,506
<i>I'm concerned that the
Receiver is becoming reckless.</i>

648
00:37:40,920 --> 00:37:43,460
<i>Are you being properly prepared?</i>

649
00:37:43,560 --> 00:37:44,540
I think so.

650
00:37:44,640 --> 00:37:46,949
<i>You're focused?</i>

651
00:37:47,680 --> 00:37:51,260
<i>Perhaps you're spending too much time
with friends from your childhood.</i>

652
00:37:51,360 --> 00:37:52,340
I'm focused.

653
00:37:52,440 --> 00:37:55,700
<i>Jonas, what do you and
the Receiver actually do?</i>

654
00:37:55,800 --> 00:37:57,420
My rules say I'm not
allowed to share.

655
00:37:57,520 --> 00:37:59,465
She is the Chief Elder.

656
00:37:59,920 --> 00:38:02,184
Jonas, she only wants to help.

657
00:38:02,600 --> 00:38:04,511
You're right.

658
00:38:05,360 --> 00:38:08,022
But you can't tell the
Receiver I told you.

659
00:38:08,960 --> 00:38:10,340
<i>You have my word.</i>

660
00:38:10,440 --> 00:38:14,300
We sit in chairs and
don't talk all day long.

661
00:38:14,400 --> 00:38:17,028
And then when time is up,
I come back here,

662
00:38:17,240 --> 00:38:20,061
and in the morning,
I do it all again.

663
00:38:22,040 --> 00:38:24,463
I apologize, but I'm late.

664
00:38:25,040 --> 00:38:27,508
<i>Your apology is accepted.</i>

665
00:38:28,920 --> 00:38:30,706
Goodbye, Mother.

666
00:38:33,800 --> 00:38:35,180
<i>Injected.</i>

667
00:38:35,280 --> 00:38:36,900
<i>He's not usually like this.</i>

668
00:38:37,000 --> 00:38:40,749
I'm surprised you're not
more worried about him.

669
00:38:42,200 --> 00:38:46,102
Were he my responsibility,
I would be.

670
00:38:46,520 --> 00:38:49,300
<i>We'd been told the Chief
Elder knew everything.</i>

671
00:38:49,400 --> 00:38:50,700
<i>Things nobody else did.</i>

672
00:38:52,160 --> 00:38:55,061
<i>But I had learned that
knowing what something is,</i>

673
00:38:55,760 --> 00:38:59,150
<i>is not the same as knowing
how something feels.</i>

674
00:39:03,440 --> 00:39:04,980
You get to be the very best,

675
00:39:05,080 --> 00:39:07,460
the last one at the
top of the mountain,

676
00:39:07,560 --> 00:39:11,540
gasping for air,
having survived, and be alone.

677
00:39:11,640 --> 00:39:12,940
Be curious.

678
00:39:13,040 --> 00:39:14,820
<i>I got lost.</i>

679
00:39:14,920 --> 00:39:16,910
<i>The good kind of lost.</i>

680
00:39:17,080 --> 00:39:19,980
<i>I saw sights and sounds I
had no words to describe.</i>

681
00:39:21,160 --> 00:39:23,540
<i>Faces with flesh of
all different colors.</i>

682
00:39:23,640 --> 00:39:25,380
<i>I felt so alive.</i>

683
00:39:25,480 --> 00:39:27,060
<i>This was forbidden?</i>

684
00:39:27,160 --> 00:39:30,311
<i>I didn't know what
to think, what to believe.</i>

685
00:39:30,840 --> 00:39:33,380
<i>Have faith, the Giver told me.</i>

686
00:39:33,480 --> 00:39:36,900
<i>He said faith,
that was seeing beyond.</i>

687
00:39:37,000 --> 00:39:40,700
<i>He compared it to the wind,
something felt but not seen.</i>

688
00:39:40,800 --> 00:39:43,060
Don't accept...

689
00:39:43,160 --> 00:39:45,300
What is the truth just because

690
00:39:45,400 --> 00:39:47,060
it's coming from someone you respect.

691
00:39:47,160 --> 00:39:48,740
I feel completely stupid.

692
00:39:48,840 --> 00:39:50,260
- I have a weird feeling.
- Weird?

693
00:39:50,360 --> 00:39:52,510
- It tingles in your hands.
- Yes.

694
00:39:52,680 --> 00:39:55,467
Memories are not just about the past,

695
00:39:55,680 --> 00:39:58,023
they determine our future.

696
00:39:58,200 --> 00:40:00,260
You can change things.

697
00:40:00,360 --> 00:40:02,749
You can make things better.

698
00:40:06,280 --> 00:40:08,464
<i>It was life.</i>

699
00:40:08,800 --> 00:40:11,587
<i>It just seemed more complete.</i>

700
00:40:13,000 --> 00:40:16,868
<i>The more I experienced,
the more I wanted.</i>

701
00:40:17,680 --> 00:40:22,071
<i>Once, there were other living things.</i>

702
00:40:22,880 --> 00:40:24,780
<i>But unlike us,</i>

703
00:40:24,880 --> 00:40:28,270
<i>they knew who their
mothers and fathers were.</i>

704
00:40:28,880 --> 00:40:31,260
<i>They had joy</i>

705
00:40:31,360 --> 00:40:33,464
and they had pain.

706
00:40:35,320 --> 00:40:37,780
I can't prepare you for
what's going to happen...

707
00:40:37,880 --> 00:40:39,340
You don't need to warn
me every single time.

708
00:40:39,440 --> 00:40:41,780
No, Jonas, you don't understand.

709
00:40:41,880 --> 00:40:43,420
There was tremendous cruelty.

710
00:40:43,520 --> 00:40:45,900
Giver, I'm not a kid any more.

711
00:40:46,000 --> 00:40:47,990
Show me.

712
00:40:56,760 --> 00:40:59,660
That's $250,000 of ivory.

713
00:40:59,760 --> 00:41:00,780
Come on!

714
00:41:00,880 --> 00:41:02,711
Come on!

715
00:41:03,120 --> 00:41:04,985
Got him!

716
00:41:09,560 --> 00:41:13,269
No, stop! Stop!

717
00:41:18,240 --> 00:41:20,026
Stop.

718
00:41:40,480 --> 00:41:41,860
Gabe.

719
00:41:41,960 --> 00:41:43,020
Hey, hey.

720
00:41:43,120 --> 00:41:44,620
Hey, hey, Gabe.

721
00:41:44,720 --> 00:41:45,740
Gabe.

722
00:41:45,840 --> 00:41:48,980
If I tell you a secret, do you
promise not to tell anyone?

723
00:41:52,600 --> 00:41:54,784
I'll take that as a yes.

724
00:41:55,080 --> 00:41:57,150
This Comfort Object

725
00:41:57,960 --> 00:41:59,985
is not a hippo.

726
00:42:00,720 --> 00:42:02,100
It's an elephant.

727
00:42:02,200 --> 00:42:05,180
And once, it was real.

728
00:42:07,400 --> 00:42:09,425
And it was beautiful.

729
00:42:27,640 --> 00:42:29,140
<i>Citizens are reminded</i>

730
00:42:29,240 --> 00:42:33,020
<i>that sleep period
commences in 15 minutes.</i>

731
00:42:33,120 --> 00:42:34,621
<i>Thank you.</i>

732
00:43:22,240 --> 00:43:25,140
It was like a memory,
but Fiona was there.

733
00:43:25,240 --> 00:43:27,071
You had a dream.

734
00:43:27,320 --> 00:43:29,300
- A what?
- A dream.

735
00:43:29,400 --> 00:43:32,780
A combination of reality,
fantasy, emotions

736
00:43:32,880 --> 00:43:34,540
and what you had for dinner.

737
00:43:39,000 --> 00:43:42,231
You've stopped taking your
injections, haven't you?

738
00:43:46,640 --> 00:43:49,380
The emotion was so strong.

739
00:43:49,480 --> 00:43:53,660
And at the wedding, everyone all
together, laughing and dancing.

740
00:43:53,760 --> 00:43:55,940
The old with the young,
the bride and the groom,

741
00:43:56,040 --> 00:43:58,349
there was something there.

742
00:43:59,320 --> 00:44:01,300
But different to what we have.

743
00:44:01,400 --> 00:44:03,026
Yes.

744
00:44:03,680 --> 00:44:06,308
We don't have that any more.

745
00:44:07,360 --> 00:44:09,340
What do you mean by "that"?

746
00:44:09,440 --> 00:44:14,423
Well, I'm talking about what
you feel for someone else.

747
00:44:15,720 --> 00:44:18,900
And the mind can't
explain it and you...

748
00:44:19,000 --> 00:44:21,060
You can't make it go away.

749
00:44:21,160 --> 00:44:22,180
What is it?

750
00:44:22,280 --> 00:44:24,191
Love.

751
00:44:25,360 --> 00:44:28,545
It's called love.

752
00:44:30,000 --> 00:44:31,786
Love.

753
00:44:34,560 --> 00:44:36,300
Oh, hi.

754
00:44:36,400 --> 00:44:37,860
Hi.

755
00:44:37,960 --> 00:44:40,428
So what's new?

756
00:44:41,400 --> 00:44:43,260
What's new with you?

757
00:44:43,360 --> 00:44:45,669
What's ever new?

758
00:44:49,360 --> 00:44:51,100
Why are you being weird?

759
00:44:51,200 --> 00:44:52,980
I'm not.

760
00:44:53,080 --> 00:44:54,866
I'm just...

761
00:44:55,200 --> 00:44:57,111
I'm just...

762
00:45:05,160 --> 00:45:07,340
Hold on to the hippo, Gabe!

763
00:45:07,440 --> 00:45:09,180
Hold on!

764
00:45:09,280 --> 00:45:11,300
Father, do you love me?

765
00:45:11,400 --> 00:45:14,380
Jonas, precision of language.

766
00:45:14,480 --> 00:45:15,540
Please.

767
00:45:15,640 --> 00:45:17,180
What does "love" mean?

768
00:45:17,280 --> 00:45:18,860
I got him, Lily.

769
00:45:18,960 --> 00:45:20,340
Jonas used a word so antiquated

770
00:45:20,440 --> 00:45:22,820
that it no longer
has any application.

771
00:45:22,920 --> 00:45:24,260
- Okay?
- Okay.

772
00:45:24,360 --> 00:45:28,501
If you asked, "Do you enjoy me?"
the answer is certainly yes.

773
00:45:28,960 --> 00:45:32,191
Or do Mother and I take pride
in your accomplishments?

774
00:45:32,640 --> 00:45:34,220
Well, of course we do.

775
00:45:34,320 --> 00:45:36,504
Do you understand?

776
00:45:37,800 --> 00:45:39,060
Yes.

777
00:45:39,160 --> 00:45:40,980
I think I finally do.

778
00:45:43,520 --> 00:45:44,540
Hey!

779
00:45:44,640 --> 00:45:47,541
