01:01:17,800 --> 01:01:19,940
Something can be done.
Something can be done.

1044
01:01:20,040 --> 01:01:21,060
What are you proposing?

1045
01:01:21,160 --> 01:01:23,660
All the memories back and back
and back can be returned.

1046
01:01:23,760 --> 01:01:24,940
I need to leave the Community.

1047
01:01:25,040 --> 01:01:26,540
I need to find the
Boundary of Memory.

1048
01:01:26,640 --> 01:01:27,620
And then?

1049
01:01:27,720 --> 01:01:28,860
And then cross it.

1050
01:01:28,960 --> 01:01:30,660
- No more discussions.
- Slowly.

1051
01:01:30,760 --> 01:01:31,740
Gabe is in danger.

1052
01:01:31,840 --> 01:01:33,500
- Slowly.
- I can't wait any more.

1053
01:01:33,600 --> 01:01:35,590
Something must be done.

1054
01:01:37,800 --> 01:01:40,180
If you had that map, then why
didn't you try to leave?

1055
01:01:40,280 --> 01:01:43,869
I was waiting for someone like you.

1056
01:01:44,040 --> 01:01:45,860
You are the reason we have a chance.

1057
01:01:45,960 --> 01:01:50,060
So, the plan will be for you
to go and for me to stay.

1058
01:01:50,160 --> 01:01:52,389
If you did cross this Boundary,

1059
01:01:52,960 --> 01:01:54,500
and if the memories were set free,

1060
01:01:54,600 --> 01:01:58,140
all of the pain that you felt,
all the confusion, the chaos,

1061
01:01:58,240 --> 01:01:59,420
it would all return.

1062
01:01:59,520 --> 01:02:02,341
- So you'd stay to help them?
- Yes.

1063
01:02:03,800 --> 01:02:05,825
And for my daughter.

1064
01:02:05,960 --> 01:02:07,780
It's what she would've wanted.

1065
01:02:07,880 --> 01:02:09,140
Your daughter?

1066
01:02:09,240 --> 01:02:10,980
Rosemary.

1067
01:02:11,080 --> 01:02:12,300
Now, your friend.

1068
01:02:12,400 --> 01:02:14,660
If he truly saw the
Triangle of Rocks...

1069
01:02:14,760 --> 01:02:18,343
Bring up Jonas's activity
for the past year as well.

1070
01:02:18,960 --> 01:02:21,540
So Asher came directly to you?

1071
01:02:21,640 --> 01:02:22,620
Yes.

1072
01:02:22,720 --> 01:02:25,420
What was Jonas's disposition
at evening meal?

1073
01:02:25,520 --> 01:02:27,100
Dissatisfied.

1074
01:02:27,200 --> 01:02:28,220
Anxious.

1075
01:02:28,320 --> 01:02:29,340
Indignant.

1076
01:02:29,440 --> 01:02:31,940
Set up a communication with
the Receiver of Memory.

1077
01:02:32,040 --> 01:02:34,860
We're not permitted to see
into the Receiver's residence.

1078
01:02:34,960 --> 01:02:36,180
We can only transmit.

1079
01:02:36,280 --> 01:02:39,500
Well, then we shall only transmit.

1080
01:02:39,600 --> 01:02:42,580
If you go, head towards the Triangle,

1081
01:02:42,680 --> 01:02:44,500
away from the other Communities.

1082
01:02:44,600 --> 01:02:46,340
That will lead to the
Boundary of Memory.

1083
01:02:46,440 --> 01:02:48,820
<i>Please stand by for a transmission.</i>

1084
01:02:48,920 --> 01:02:50,780
<i>I apologize for the intrusion.</i>

1085
01:02:50,880 --> 01:02:53,189
I accept your apology.

1086
01:02:53,320 --> 01:02:57,220
<i>We have a problem.
The Receiver-in-Training is missing,</i>

1087
01:02:57,320 --> 01:03:00,100
<i>and he physically attacked
his friend, Asher.</i>

1088
01:03:00,200 --> 01:03:01,660
He did?

1089
01:03:01,760 --> 01:03:02,780
That's serious.

1090
01:03:02,880 --> 01:03:05,667
<i>Do you know where Jonas is?</i>

1091
01:03:07,440 --> 01:03:09,180
I do not.

1092
01:03:12,840 --> 01:03:13,980
Well, thank you very much

1093
01:03:14,080 --> 01:03:17,740
for helping us to narrow
down the possibilities.

1094
01:03:17,840 --> 01:03:19,900
<i>I will contact you if he comes here.</i>

1095
01:03:20,000 --> 01:03:22,628
<i>Only if it's not an imposition.</i>

1096
01:03:23,080 --> 01:03:24,706
<i>Thank you.</i>

1097
01:03:27,160 --> 01:03:28,940
He's lying.

1098
01:03:29,040 --> 01:03:30,060
Talk!

1099
01:03:30,160 --> 01:03:31,660
They're going to kill Gabe.

1100
01:03:31,760 --> 01:03:34,980
I'm leaving, I'm leaving tonight,
and I'm going to take him with me.

1101
01:03:35,080 --> 01:03:36,940
Jonas, not yet, you're not ready.

1102
01:03:37,040 --> 01:03:40,544
When they decided to kill Gabe,
they decided I was ready.

1103
01:03:46,000 --> 01:03:47,420
I like this map.

1104
01:03:47,520 --> 01:03:48,500
Don't mess it up.

1105
01:03:48,600 --> 01:03:50,431
I'll be wanting it back.

1106
01:03:53,720 --> 01:03:57,463
You don't mind if I accelerate
your training a bit, do you?

1107
01:04:00,600 --> 01:04:03,340
You'd think for someone who
is the keeper of emotions,

1108
01:04:03,440 --> 01:04:05,704
that I'd be better at...

1109
01:04:06,920 --> 01:04:08,421
Well...

1110
01:04:09,080 --> 01:04:12,106
I love you, Jonas.

1111
01:04:14,120 --> 01:04:16,668
There. There it is.

1112
01:04:18,240 --> 01:04:19,740
You have the courage.

1113
01:04:19,840 --> 01:04:23,025
- Let me give you the strength.
- Can I just...

1114
01:04:49,320 --> 01:04:51,220
<i>Attention all Community residents,</i>

1115
01:04:51,320 --> 01:04:53,820
<i>the Receiver-in-Training
has been reported missing</i>

1116
01:04:53,920 --> 01:04:55,260
<i>from his dwelling.</i>

1117
01:04:55,360 --> 01:04:56,820
<i>Please, be alert.</i>

1118
01:04:56,920 --> 01:04:58,467
<i>He may be in danger.</i>

1119
01:05:04,800 --> 01:05:07,260
The Group One will start from
the Edge and work inward.

1120
01:05:07,360 --> 01:05:09,544
And then Group Two
from the center out.

1121
01:05:09,680 --> 01:05:11,705
No, no, like this.

1122
01:05:14,760 --> 01:05:17,740
<i>Welcome to the Nurturing Center.</i>

1123
01:05:22,400 --> 01:05:24,460
- Shall I convene the Elders?
- Yes.

1124
01:05:27,080 --> 01:05:28,260
Jonas!

1125
01:05:28,360 --> 01:05:29,340
I heard an alert.

1126
01:05:29,440 --> 01:05:30,420
What's going on?

1127
01:05:30,520 --> 01:05:31,500
Hey, where's Gabe?

1128
01:05:31,600 --> 01:05:32,580
Is he here?

1129
01:05:32,680 --> 01:05:34,140
- Is he in one of these?
- If he's back,

1130
01:05:34,240 --> 01:05:37,860
then he'd be with the Uncertains
on a restricted floor.

1131
01:05:37,960 --> 01:05:39,621
Show me where.

1132
01:05:40,200 --> 01:05:41,826
Fiona, please.

1133
01:05:44,080 --> 01:05:45,980
They're downstairs. Come on.

1134
01:05:46,080 --> 01:05:48,820
<i>Jonas was chosen for the
most important position</i>

1135
01:05:48,920 --> 01:05:51,460
<i>in our Community.</i>

1136
01:05:51,560 --> 01:05:54,620
He was asked if he
were strong enough.

1137
01:05:54,720 --> 01:05:56,420
It turns out he was not.

1138
01:05:56,520 --> 01:05:59,100
<i>Instead, he is a rebel</i>

1139
01:05:59,200 --> 01:06:02,740
<i>who must be stopped by you.</i>

1140
01:06:02,840 --> 01:06:04,910
<i>When you find him,</i>

1141
01:06:05,840 --> 01:06:07,380
take him.

1142
01:06:07,480 --> 01:06:08,460
Gabe is in danger.

1143
01:06:08,560 --> 01:06:11,260
- Jonas, he's fine, I'll show you.
- No, he's not fine.

1144
01:06:11,360 --> 01:06:12,580
He should be here.

1145
01:06:12,680 --> 01:06:15,100
Fiona, I'm leaving tonight.

1146
01:06:15,200 --> 01:06:16,980
Leaving? What do you mean?

1147
01:06:17,080 --> 01:06:19,620
I'm taking Gabe.
We're leaving the Community.

1148
01:06:19,720 --> 01:06:21,380
I want you to come with us.

1149
01:06:26,680 --> 01:06:27,980
There you go.

1150
01:06:28,080 --> 01:06:29,100
There you go.

1151
01:06:32,560 --> 01:06:36,109
<i>I don't have the
words to describe it.</i>

1152
01:06:40,760 --> 01:06:42,780
<i>Fiona, there is more.</i>

1153
01:06:42,880 --> 01:06:44,745
<i>So much more.</i>

1154
01:06:48,280 --> 01:06:49,660
What are they doing?

1155
01:06:49,760 --> 01:06:51,380
<i>Fiona, what do you feel?</i>

1156
01:06:51,480 --> 01:06:53,980
<i>I don't have the
words to describe it.</i>

1157
01:06:54,080 --> 01:06:56,105
<i>Attention, Nurturers.</i>

1158
01:06:56,840 --> 01:06:59,660
<i>Please secure your work
area and immediately report</i>

1159
01:06:59,760 --> 01:07:04,185
<i>to the Newborns Nursery to allow
for a security search procedure.</i>

1160
01:07:04,640 --> 01:07:09,111
<i>Promptly report all sightings
at the nearest security kiosk.</i>

1161
01:07:09,240 --> 01:07:10,866
<i>Thank you.</i>

1162
01:07:22,240 --> 01:07:24,620
Fiona, we got to go now.
You, me and Gabe.

1163
01:07:24,720 --> 01:07:27,140
Jonas, I can't.
What about my family unit?

1164
01:07:27,240 --> 01:07:29,071
The other Newchildren?

1165
01:07:29,200 --> 01:07:31,540
- I can't leave them.
- This is the only way.

1166
01:07:31,640 --> 01:07:34,586
This is the only way to
make everything okay.

1167
01:07:37,160 --> 01:07:39,264
I can't go.

1168
01:07:41,560 --> 01:07:43,903
When I get there, you'll understand.

1169
01:07:44,320 --> 01:07:45,380
I'll come back for you.

1170
01:07:45,480 --> 01:07:47,061
Jonas!

1171
01:07:52,560 --> 01:07:54,540
<i>We're checking the Nurturing Center.</i>

1172
01:07:54,640 --> 01:07:56,551
Come back.

1173
01:07:57,360 --> 01:07:58,420
Now go, Jonas!

1174
01:07:59,960 --> 01:08:02,300
Please! Stop!
She's in corridor three!

1175
01:09:55,800 --> 01:09:57,940
<i>Subject lost to the Edge.</i>

1176
01:09:58,040 --> 01:09:59,871
<i>Search terminated.</i>

1177
01:10:00,000 --> 01:10:01,740
And I asked why he was out so late.

1178
01:10:01,840 --> 01:10:04,140
He seemed angry.

1179
01:10:04,240 --> 01:10:07,830
I didn't understand why,
but I wanted to help him.

1180
01:10:08,240 --> 01:10:10,260
He hit me, and at first...

1181
01:10:10,360 --> 01:10:11,940
I can tell why you've
been acting this way.

1182
01:10:12,040 --> 01:10:15,191
Your injection levels
are extremely low.

1183
01:10:17,800 --> 01:10:19,580
I can correct this.

1184
01:10:19,680 --> 01:10:21,864
Friends forever, right?

1185
01:10:23,960 --> 01:10:27,304
And then we will address
what's happened.

1186
01:10:39,760 --> 01:10:41,460
<i>When I went over the Edge,</i>

1187
01:10:41,560 --> 01:10:43,340
<i>we shouldn't have made it.</i>

1188
01:10:43,440 --> 01:10:45,820
<i>This was a miracle.</i>

1189
01:10:45,920 --> 01:10:48,420
<i>The Giver had talked about them.</i>

1190
01:10:48,520 --> 01:10:51,830
<i>He told me I could draw
strength from the memories.</i>

1191
01:10:52,920 --> 01:10:55,741
<i>I knew by giving them to Gabe,</i>

1192
01:10:56,080 --> 01:10:58,628
<i>I could protect him.</i>

1193
01:11:02,480 --> 01:11:04,460
<i>Prick your finger and put a
little blood on this apple.</i>

1194
01:11:04,560 --> 01:11:07,180
<i>When you leave in the morning,
put the apple over the sensor.</i>

1195
01:11:07,280 --> 01:11:09,900
<i>I've been doing it for months,
and it's worked every single time.</i>

1196
01:11:10,000 --> 01:11:12,707
What has he taught you?

1197
01:11:13,600 --> 01:11:14,620
<i>This is the only way.</i>

1198
01:11:14,720 --> 01:11:16,620
<i>This is the only way to
make everything okay.</i>

1199
01:11:16,720 --> 01:11:17,980
<i>Gabe is in danger.</i>

1200
01:11:18,080 --> 01:11:20,180
<i>What they're gonna
do to him is really bad.</i>

1201
01:11:20,280 --> 01:11:22,260
<i>I want you to come with us.</i>

1202
01:11:22,360 --> 01:11:24,180
<i>When I get there, you'll understand.</i>

1203
01:11:24,280 --> 01:11:26,380
<i>I'll come back for you.</i>

1204
01:11:26,480 --> 01:11:28,061
Yes.

1205
01:11:32,640 --> 01:11:34,380
Careful.

1206
01:11:34,600 --> 01:11:36,226
Careful.

1207
01:11:38,640 --> 01:11:42,140
I apologize for failing again.

1208
01:11:42,240 --> 01:11:43,980
I don't think you failed.

1209
01:11:44,080 --> 01:11:47,700
I think you succeeded with your plan.

1210
01:11:47,800 --> 01:11:50,540
Ever since the girl was Released,
you haven't been the same.

1211
01:11:50,640 --> 01:11:53,860
I genuinely hoped
Jonas would help you.

1212
01:11:53,960 --> 01:11:55,260
You'd have a fresh start.

1213
01:11:55,360 --> 01:11:57,828
The two of you would work together.

1214
01:11:59,400 --> 01:12:01,584
Which, it seems, you have.

1215
01:12:02,120 --> 01:12:04,270
We will find Jonas.

1216
01:12:31,880 --> 01:12:34,340
<i>Jonas, our Receiver of Memory,</i>

1217
01:12:34,440 --> 01:12:35,900
<i>lost to the Edge.</i>

1218
01:12:36,000 --> 01:12:39,540
Jonas, Jonas, Jonas, Jonas, Jonas,

1219
01:12:39,640 --> 01:12:42,100
Jonas, Jonas, Jonas,

1220
01:12:42,200 --> 01:12:43,700
Jonas, Jonas,

1221
01:12:43,800 --> 01:12:46,060
Jonas, Jonas, Jonas...

1222
01:12:46,160 --> 01:12:47,940
How do they know Jonas is gone?

1223
01:12:48,040 --> 01:12:50,420
We must not say his name any more.

1224
01:12:50,520 --> 01:12:52,180
I will.

1225
01:12:52,280 --> 01:12:53,820
You have to be quiet now, Lily.

1226
01:12:53,920 --> 01:12:55,980
Jonas, Jonas...

1227
01:12:56,080 --> 01:12:58,020
And a hippo is really an elephant.

1228
01:12:58,120 --> 01:13:02,625
Jonas, Jonas, Jonas, Jonas, Jonas...

1229
01:13:08,200 --> 01:13:12,020
What I'm about to tell you,
you must never repeat to anyone.

1230
01:13:12,120 --> 01:13:14,300
I don't believe Jonas is Lost.

1231
01:13:14,400 --> 01:13:16,500
But the Ceremony of Loss?

1232
01:13:16,600 --> 01:13:18,540
A charade.

1233
01:13:18,640 --> 01:13:20,340
I don't expect you to understand,

1234
01:13:20,440 --> 01:13:23,940
but you must know that Jonas
has become dangerous.

1235
01:13:24,040 --> 01:13:25,700
He must be stopped.

1236
01:13:25,800 --> 01:13:29,144
He must not get beyond
the Triangle of Rocks.

1237
01:13:29,320 --> 01:13:31,260
What do you want me to do?

1238
01:13:31,360 --> 01:13:33,060
You know Jonas.

1239
01:13:33,160 --> 01:13:34,991
I want you to find him.

1240
01:13:37,760 --> 01:13:39,500
And then...

1241
01:13:39,720 --> 01:13:42,222
I want you to lose him.

1242
01:15:00,800 --> 01:15:02,340
Jonas.

1243
01:15:02,440 --> 01:15:06,103
- What are you doing?
<i>- Asher, please, let us go.</i>

1244
01:15:07,160 --> 01:15:08,180
I can't.

1245
01:15:08,280 --> 01:15:09,300
I'm supposed to...

1246
01:15:09,400 --> 01:15:11,311
<i>To what?</i>

1247
01:15:12,760 --> 01:15:14,705
To lose you.

1248
01:15:16,880 --> 01:15:19,100
Asher, if you are my friend,

1249
01:15:19,200 --> 01:15:21,300
<i>if you ever were my friend,</i>

1250
01:15:21,400 --> 01:15:23,460
<i>can you please somehow trust me?</i>

1251
01:15:23,560 --> 01:15:25,744
Trust me now.

1252
01:16:09,160 --> 01:16:10,991
I do trust you, Jonas.

1253
01:16:22,240 --> 01:16:24,504
Come on, please.

1254
01:16:26,800 --> 01:16:28,665
Jonas.

1255
01:16:46,200 --> 01:16:48,145
<i>You found him.</i>

1256
01:16:49,640 --> 01:16:51,260
I did.

1257
01:16:51,360 --> 01:16:53,430
<i>For the good of all of us,</i>

1258
01:16:53,720 --> 01:16:55,506
<i>I beg you,</i>

1259
01:16:55,680 --> 01:16:57,784
finish this.

1260
01:16:58,000 --> 01:16:59,706
It's finished.

1261
01:17:15,040 --> 01:17:16,985
Hey.

1262
01:17:17,400 --> 01:17:19,504
It's okay.

1263
01:17:27,840 --> 01:17:29,540
<i>Nothing the Giver had shown me</i>

1264
01:17:29,640 --> 01:17:32,020
<i>had prepared me for
the voices in my head,</i>

1265
01:17:32,120 --> 01:17:34,622
<i>screaming at me to stop.</i>

1266
01:17:35,000 --> 01:17:38,026
<i>But I knew Fiona would be
punished for helping me,</i>

1267
01:17:38,160 --> 01:17:40,662
<i>Asher, for letting me go.</i>

1268
01:17:40,880 --> 01:17:42,180
<i>The only way to help them,</i>

1269
01:17:42,280 --> 01:17:44,620
<i>to keep them alive,</i>

1270
01:17:44,720 --> 01:17:49,749
<i>Was to get to the Boundary,
if it even existed.</i>

1271
01:17:51,720 --> 01:17:54,660
<i>I strengthened Gabe with
memories of having enough</i>

1272
01:17:54,760 --> 01:17:56,910
<i>and knowing joy.</i>

1273
01:18:00,160 --> 01:18:03,061
<i>It was the memory of Fiona
that kept me going.</i>

1274
01:18:13,360 --> 01:18:15,191
Fiona?

1275
01:18:17,680 --> 01:18:19,420
I've taken care of everything.

1276
01:18:19,520 --> 01:18:21,420
We've arranged for your Release.

1277
01:18:21,520 --> 01:18:23,060
There'll be a nice ceremony.

1278
01:18:23,160 --> 01:18:25,503
Now, you get some rest.

1279
01:18:26,000 --> 01:18:27,780
- I felt things.
- What?

1280
01:18:27,880 --> 01:18:29,420
I know that there's something more.

1281
01:18:29,520 --> 01:18:32,620
- Fiona...
- Something missing from our lives.

1282
01:18:32,720 --> 01:18:33,860
No, not missing.

1283
01:18:33,960 --> 01:18:38,624
Something that has been
stolen from me and from you.

1284
01:18:38,800 --> 01:18:41,302
I don't know what it is exactly,

1285
01:18:42,320 --> 01:18:44,470
but Jonas does.

1286
01:18:45,400 --> 01:18:51,745
I have felt things, and they
were warm, and they were nice.

1287
01:18:53,760 --> 01:18:56,103
They were beautiful.

1288
01:18:56,240 --> 01:18:58,180
I have felt things.

1289
01:18:58,280 --> 01:19:00,066
I have felt things.

1290
01:19:00,920 --> 01:19:03,149
I have felt things.

1291
01:19:50,520 --> 01:19:53,022
Where is the tower, Gabe?

1292
01:19:54,320 --> 01:19:56,948
The tower should be here.

1293
01:20:55,360 --> 01:20:57,146
You can stop this.

1294
01:20:57,320 --> 01:20:59,140
Stop what?

1295
01:20:59,240 --> 01:21:03,030
If you don't want to see it,
sit down with the other Elders.

1296
01:21:03,200 --> 01:21:05,384
Close your eyes.

1297
01:21:09,200 --> 01:21:13,227
<i>Ceremony of Release to Elsewhere.</i>

1298
01:21:14,400 --> 01:21:15,860
Hello, Fiona.

1299
01:21:17,800 --> 01:21:19,825
You uncomfortable?

1300
01:21:25,920 --> 01:21:27,780
I'm not uncomfortable.

1301
01:21:27,880 --> 01:21:29,825
I'm afraid.

1302
01:21:30,320 --> 01:21:32,549
You don't have to be afraid.

1303
01:21:32,800 --> 01:21:34,580
You know me.

1304
01:21:34,680 --> 01:21:36,460
I'll be very gentle.

1305
01:21:36,560 --> 01:21:38,340
I promise.

1306
01:21:38,440 --> 01:21:40,101
Okay?

1307
01:21:42,400 --> 01:21:44,900
Her name was Rosemary.

1308
01:21:45,000 --> 01:21:46,940
She was my daughter.

1309
01:21:47,040 --> 01:21:48,060
I loved her.

1310
01:21:48,160 --> 01:21:49,380
Precision of language.

1311
01:21:49,480 --> 01:21:52,180
I could not be more precise.

1312
01:21:52,280 --> 01:21:54,748
Do you know what that's like?

1313
01:21:55,840 --> 01:21:57,705
To love someone?

1314
01:21:58,400 --> 01:22:00,140
I do.

1315
01:22:04,200 --> 01:22:07,820
<i>I've cried, felt true sorrow.</i>

1316
01:22:07,920 --> 01:22:10,229
<i>I've sung, danced.</i>

1317
01:22:11,440 --> 01:22:13,820
I've felt real joy.

1318
01:22:13,920 --> 01:22:16,260
Then you should know

1319
01:22:16,360 --> 01:22:19,261
better than anyone.

1320
01:22:20,080 --> 01:22:22,660
You have seen children starve.

1321
01:22:23,920 --> 01:22:27,220
You've seen people stand
on each other's necks

1322
01:22:27,320 --> 01:22:29,584
just for the view.

1323
01:22:30,200 --> 01:22:33,380
You know what it feels like
when men blow each other up.

1324
01:22:33,480 --> 01:22:34,460
Yes.

1325
01:22:34,560 --> 01:22:36,460
Over a simple line in the sand.

1326
01:22:36,560 --> 01:22:37,820
I do, I do, but...

1327
01:22:37,920 --> 01:22:39,340
And yet...

1328
01:22:39,440 --> 01:22:40,620
And yet,

1329
01:22:40,720 --> 01:22:43,140
you and Jonas want to

1330
01:22:43,240 --> 01:22:44,820
<i>open that door again,</i>

1331
01:22:44,920 --> 01:22:46,260
bring all that back.

1332
01:22:46,360 --> 01:22:49,020
If you could only see
the possibility of love.

1333
01:22:49,120 --> 01:22:50,820
- Why?
- Of love.

1334
01:22:50,920 --> 01:22:52,540
- Love is just...
- With love comes faith,

1335
01:22:52,640 --> 01:22:53,620
with it comes hope.

1336
01:22:53,720 --> 01:22:56,871
Love is just passion that can turn.

1337
01:22:57,000 --> 01:22:58,580
We can do better.

1338
01:22:58,680 --> 01:23:00,100
It turns into contempt and murder.

1339
01:23:00,200 --> 01:23:01,740
We could choose better.

1340
01:23:04,400 --> 01:23:05,540
People are weak.

1341
01:23:05,640 --> 01:23:08,029
People are selfish.

1342
01:23:09,040 --> 01:23:13,620
When people have the freedom
to choose, they choose wrong

1343
01:23:13,800 --> 01:23:16,029
every single time.

1344
01:24:35,960 --> 01:24:37,825
It's a sled.

1345
01:24:39,840 --> 01:24:42,820
<i>Loss and pain,</i>

1346
01:24:43,400 --> 01:24:44,700
music,

1347
01:24:44,800 --> 01:24:46,220
Joy,

1348
01:24:46,320 --> 01:24:49,700
the raw, impossible,

1349
01:24:49,800 --> 01:24:51,620
beautiful feeling of love.

1350
01:24:51,720 --> 01:24:54,100
Your son, he felt that.

1351
01:25:10,000 --> 01:25:12,940
That girl, she has felt it.

1352
01:25:13,040 --> 01:25:14,020
That's enough.

1353
01:25:14,120 --> 01:25:19,140
We are living a life of
shadows, of echoes, of faint,

1354
01:25:19,240 --> 01:25:21,900
distant whispers of
what once made us real.

1355
01:25:22,000 --> 01:25:24,070
Excuse me for one second, Fiona.

1356
01:25:24,240 --> 01:25:26,230
<i>We must continue.</i>

1357
01:27:07,760 --> 01:27:09,220
<i>I wish I had been there</i>

1358
01:27:09,320 --> 01:27:11,470
<i>when the memories returned.</i>

1359
01:27:11,680 --> 01:27:13,944
<i>They were the truth.</i>

1360
01:27:14,120 --> 01:27:16,827
<i>The Elders and their
rules were the lie.</i>

1361
01:27:18,400 --> 01:27:20,664
<i>So I do not apologize.</i>

1362
01:27:25,080 --> 01:27:27,150
<i>I knew Fiona was safe,</i>

1363
01:27:27,400 --> 01:27:29,265
<i>that I'd see her again,</i>

1364
01:27:30,000 --> 01:27:32,260
<i>and that I held the
future there in my arms.</i>

1365
01:27:36,960 --> 01:27:41,985
<i>The Giver had led us
here to this house.</i>

1366
01:27:42,360 --> 01:27:44,066
<i>It was real.</i>

1367
01:27:46,400 --> 01:27:50,309
<i>From far behind me,
from the place I had left,</i>

1368
01:27:50,520 --> 01:27:53,022
<i>I thought I heard music, too.</i>

1369
01:27:54,320 --> 01:27:56,584
<i>Perhaps it was only an echo,</i>

1370
01:27:57,600 --> 01:27:59,545
<i>but it was enough.</i>

1371
01:28:00,520 --> 01:28:02,829
<i>It would lead us all home.</i>